UC-01 Fully Dressed Use Case Scenario
ID: UC-01
Title: Create Task
Description: This use case describes how the user creates a new task in 
the Personal Task Management System in order to organize and track personal work or 
activities over time.
Primary Actor: User
Preconditions: 
    - The system is running and online
    - The user is on a screen where task creation is available
Inputs:
  - The title of the task
  - Any additional information in the description
  - The priority level of the tasks
  - The date the task must be completed by (optional)
Outputs:
  - The new tasks that have been created properly saved to the system
  - A confirmation that the task was created
Main Success Scenario:
  1. The user selects the option Create Task.
  2. The system brings the task creation form into display.
  3. The user inputs the title of the task, any additional description, the priority level of
  the task, and optionally the date the task should be completed by.
  4. The user submits the task creation request to the system.
  5. The system validates the provided information.
  6. The system creates a new task with the creation date set to the current
  time and status set to open.
  7. The system records the conducted activity with a timestamp.
  8. The system confirms the successful creation of the task and displays a message with
  the task details.

Alternative Failure Scenario:
  5a. The task title is missing or invalid
    1. The system detects that the task title is missing or invalid.
    2. The request for task creation is rejected by the system.
    3. The system displays an error message on screen indicating that a
    valid title is required.
    4. There is no task created and no activity entry recorded.
